idCitation.resTitle: CNTR regions and boundaries Link table at 20M scale

dataIdInfo.idAbs: This table is an attribute table to identify the CNTR Boundaries from the feature class CNTR_BN_20M_2010 that make up a specific CNTR region in the feature class CNTR_RG_20M_2010 (topological relationship table between regions and boundaries of the CNTR_2010 20M dataset).
dataIdInfo.idPurp: This table forms the link between the feature classes CNTR_RG_20M_2010 and CNTR_BN_20M_2010. The M-N relationship between the feature classes becomes 1-M and N-1 through this table. For each CNTR region you can identify the boundaries it is made of and for each boundary line you can identify the regions that are on both sides of the border.

dataLineage.statement:
This dataset (together with the other datasets: NUTS_2010, CNTR_2010, COMM_2010, EEZ_2010 and COAS_2010) is based on geometry of EBM_v5 of EuroGeographics on commune level with a resolution of 30m (scale 1:100.000) enriched with some other datasources like Gaul 2008 country data and ArcWorld data. This resulted in a common repository of geometry of which the different datasets were derived. The different scale levels were derived of generalizations of the common repository on 100K scale. This means that within each scale level the feature classes of all these datasets: COMM_2010, NUTS_2010, CNTR_2010 and COAS_2010, are fully coherent and compliant.
The 1M scale level in the CNTR_2010 dataset consists of 2 feature classes (regions and boundaries) The boundaries and regions are related to each other through a relationship table (CNTR_RG_BN_20M_2010). In addition to the region and boundary feature classes there is also 1 label feature class which is scale independent. For each CNTR in the region feature classes there is exactly 1 label . The extent of this feature class is the world.
2014-01-10 - Errors in data resolved. Mayotte now an overseas department of France and therefore merged with the France polygon. Saint Barth√©lemy now an overseas collectivity of France and is removed from the France record and a new record with the ISO code BL is created.

prcStep.description: For each commune region in the feature class CNTR_RG_20M_2010 the bordering lines in the feature class CNTR_BN_20M_2010 were identified by making use of a spatial selection. This result was written to the CNTR_RG_BN_20M_2010.

dataSource.srcDesc:
(i) Eurogeographics EBM v5.0.(scale 1:100K) (ii) GAUL 2008 country level data (iii) NSI of TR for the Turkish features (v) GRO (General Register Office for Scotland) -- for scale level 100K (vi) NUTS nomenclature supplied by EUROSTAT -- for all scale levels
This feature class is created from a generalization of this common repository
